  "prompt": "Do landlords actually call employers for background checks?",
  "response": "Yes, many landlords do contact employers as part of the tenant screening process, which often includes background checks. This is typically done to verify a potential tenant's employment status and income level, ensuring that they have a reliable source of income to pay rent. \n\nLandlords may ask for permission from the applicant to contact their employer, and they might verify details like job title, duration of employment, and salary. This step helps landlords assess the financial stability of prospective tenants and reduce the risk of rental payment issues.\n\nHowever, not all landlords may follow the same procedures, and some may rely on other methods of verification, such as payslips, tax documents, or bank statements. It can vary depending on the landlord or property management company's policies.",
